comments:
That part which until 1.4.1935 formed part of the parish of Westmill. 
    See also Table 2, note (c).
Created 1.4.1937 out of the parishes of Layston, Aspenden, Wyddial and Throcking.

Transferred from Essex to Cambridgeshire on 30.9.1895. Renamed 
    26.1.1929 to become the parish of Great Chishill.

Created 26.1.1929 by renaming the parish of Great Chishall. See 
    also Table 2, note (b).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and added to the parish of Hormead. See 
    also Table 2, note (a).

Transferred from Essex to Cambridgeshire on 30.9.1895. See also 
    Table 2, note (b).

Created 1.4.1937 out of the parishes of Great Hormead, Little 
    Hormead, Layston and Braughing. See also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of Buntingford, 
    Hormead and Wyddial. See also Table 2, note (a).

Transferred from Essex to Cambridgeshire on 30.9.1895. See also 
    Table 2, note (b).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and added to the parish of Hormead. See 
    also Table 2, note (a).

Created 30.9.1896 from the Cambridgeshire part of the parish of 
    Royston. Abolished 1.10.1897 and added to the parish of Royston.

On 30.9.1896 the part in Cambridgeshire  became the  parish of North Royston, so that thereafter Royston was 
    entirely in Hertfordshire. See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 30.9.1896 out of the parish of Bassingbourn. Abolished 
    1.10.1897 and added to the parish of Royston.

Created 30.9.1896 out of the parish of Kneesworth. Abolished 1.10.1897 
    and added to the parish of Royston.

Created 30.9.1896 out of the parish of Melbourn. Abolished 1.10.1897 
    and added to the parish of Royston.

Abolished 25.3.1883 and added to the parish of Westmill. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).
